-- Copper Futures Advance as Much as 0.4% in New York on Outlook for Demand
-- Wendy Pugh
-- 2010-07-11T22:15:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-11/copper-futures-advance-as-much-as-0-4-in-new-york-on-outlook-for-demand.html

          
          
             Copper futures in New York rallied
as much as 0.4 percent to $3.0650 a pound before trading little
changed at $3.05 at 8:12 a.m. Melbourne time. The September-
delivery contract rose 1.3 percent on July 9 and rallied 4.7
percent last week.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Wendy Pugh in Melbourne at 
 wpugh@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        